    "effect": {
      "1": "{{NAME}} sometimes becomes someone else: <strong>{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}}</strong>.{{BR}}{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} has an entirely different personality — including tastes, hobbies, and Aspiration — but it largely takes a live-and-let-live approach to their shared body: It won't ruin {{NAME}}'s life as long as {{NAME}} does it the same courtesy. Aside from the difference in Aspiration, {{NAME}} and {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} share all Attributes, Skills, and other traits. Each remembers what the other persona does, but only vaguely or as dreams. {{NAME}}'s player should control the character even when {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} manifests, although the Storyteller should feel free to feed {{him}} information only {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} would know.{{BR}}{{NAME}} may accept a Beat to change personas at a time when doing so creates a significant complication for {{him}} or {{his}} cohort — whether this places the {{NAME}} or {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} in command.{{OPTIONLIST:this.selectedDeviations}}",
      "2": "{{NAME}} sometimes becomes someone else: <strong>{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}}</strong>.{{BR}}{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} has an entirely different personality — including tastes, hobbies, and Aspiration — but it largely takes a live-and-let-live approach to their shared body: It won't ruin {{NAME}}'s life as long as {{NAME}} does it the same courtesy. Aside from the difference in Aspiration, {{NAME}} and {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} share all Attributes, Skills, and other traits. Each remembers what the other persona does, but only vaguely or as dreams. {{NAME}}'s player should control the character even when {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} manifests, although the Storyteller should feel free to feed {{him}} information only {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} would know.{{BR}}{{NAME}} may accept a Beat to change personas at a time when doing so creates a significant complication for {{him}} or {{his}} cohort — whether this places the {{NAME}} or {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} in command.{{BR}}Once per chapter, at a time of the Storyteller's choosing, {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} takes control for <strong>{{CALC:6 - {{VALUE:scarResistance}}}} minutes</strong> (turns, in action scenes). {{NAME}} may resist this transformation with a successful {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll. If this roll succeeds, the Storyteller may make another attempt in a later scene but may not attempt to trigger this Scar again during the current scene. Each consecutive successful roll to resist transformation imposes a -1 penalty on future such rolls.{{OPTIONLIST:this.selectedDeviations}}",
      "3": "{{NAME}} sometimes becomes someone else: <strong>{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}}</strong>.{{BR}}{{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} has an entirely different personality — including tastes, hobbies, and Aspiration — but it largely takes a live-and-let-live approach to their shared body: It won't ruin {{NAME}}'s life as long as {{NAME}} does it the same courtesy. Aside from the difference in Aspiration, {{NAME}} and {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} share all Attributes, Skills, and other traits. Each remembers what the other persona does, but only vaguely or as dreams. {{NAME}}'s player should control the character even when {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} manifests, although the Storyteller should feel free to feed {{him}} information only {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} would know.{{BR}}{{NAME}} may accept a Beat to change personas at a time when doing so creates a significant complication for {{him}} or {{his}} cohort — whether this places the {{NAME}} or {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} in command. Once per chapter, at a time of the Storyteller's choosing, {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} takes control unless {{NAME}} resists the transformation with a successful {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll. If this roll succeeds, the Storyteller may make another attempt in a later scene but may not attempt to trigger this Scar again during the current scene. Each consecutive successful roll to resist transformation imposes a -1 penalty on future such rolls.{{BR}}There is no limit to how long {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} retains control: Hours or even days may pass between transformations, with {{NAME}} and {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} enjoying nearly equal time in charge of {{NAME}}'s body. {{NAME}} may attempt to reassert temporary control lasting {{VALUE:scarResistance}} minutes/turns}} up to once per scene with a successful Scar Resistance roll. Each consecutive successful roll to reassert control imposes a -1 penalty on future such rolls.{{OPTIONLIST:this.selectedDeviations}}"
    },
    "options": {
      "invoked": "<strong>Deviation -- Invoked:</strong> {{NAME}} may voluntary yield control of her body to {{DISPLAY:vars.alterEgoName}} as an action. This requires a turn in action scenes (a minute, in non-action scenes) and lasts the normal length of time based on Magnitude. This doesn't count toward the Storyteller's once-per-chapter limit.",
