  "hubris": {
    "key": "hubris",
    "name": "Hubris",
    "activation": "persistent",
    "keywords": [
      "mental",
      "social",
      "subtle"
    ],
    "value": {
      "min": 1,
      "max": 5
    },
    "effect": "{{NAME}} is certain {{he's}} the smartest one in the room and that there is no problem that {{his}} intelligence and Variations can't overcome if {{he}} puts {{his}} mind to it. Moreover, {{he}} wants everyone else to know it.{{BR}}{{NAME}} is prone to gloat over {{his}} successes (and any enemies in {{his}} power), to brag about {{his}} intelligence and Variations, and to talk about {{his}} plans even to enemies. Whenever this causes a complication for {{him}} or {{his}} cohort, {{he}} takes a Beat.{{OPTIONLIST:vars.options}}",
    "options": {
      "brag": "Whenever someone asks {{NAME}} about himself, {{he}} must make a successful {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll to resist the urge to openly hint either at {{his}} Variations, {{his}} shocking plans for the future, or {{his}} past crimes.{{BR}}{{NAME}} need not be blunt or specific — particularly if doing so in present company is a bad idea, such as when {{he}} is being interrogated by the police — but anyone reading between the lines should be able to glean enough information from {{his}} not-quite-confession to pursue further lines of inquiry.",
      "toy": "Whenever {{NAME}} has an enemy in {{his}} power — whether because they surrendered or were incapacitated — {{he}} must make a successful {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll in order to kill them or let them die.{{BR}}If {{NAME}} lets them live, {{he}} cannot simply keep them prisoner or hand them over to someone else. {{He}} must either give them an opportunity to win their freedom (which need not be fair but must not assure their failure), or contrive a satisfying and elaborate method of execution that incidentally gives them a chance to escape.{{BR}}This does not affect {{NAME}}'s ability or willingness to kill a Conviction Touchstone out of hand.",
      "boast": "Whenever someone asks {{NAME}} about himself, {{he}} must at least hint at {{his}} Variations, {{his}} shocking plans for the future, or {{his}} past crimes.{{BR}}{{NAME}} need not be blunt or specific — <em>unless</em> asked a direct question about any of the secret topics, in which case {{he}} must make a successful {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll or lay out the truth in excruciating detail even when doing so is a terrible idea.",
      "gloat": "Whenever {{NAME}} has an enemy in {{his}} power — whether because they surrendered or were incapacitated — {{he}} must free them a short while later, usually after regaling them with lengthy monologues meant to impress upon them how intelligent and powerful {{he}} is.{{BR}}Conviction Touchstones are an exception to the above: {{NAME}} may make a {{TOOLTIP:Scar Resistance,json.rules.scarResistanceRoll}} roll to kill them or let them die.{{BR}}If {{NAME}} lets them live, {{he}} cannot simply keep them prisoner or hand them over to someone else. {{He}} must either give them an opportunity to win their freedom (which need not be fair but must not assure their failure), or contrive a satisfying and elaborate method of execution that incidentally gives them a chance to escape.",
      "callingCard": "<strong>Deviation -- Calling Card:</strong> {{NAME}} feels compelled to {{SWITCH:vars.callingCardType,trophy,take trophies,callingCard,leave a calling card}} whenever {{he}} makes a significant accomplishment: {{DISPLAY:vars.callingCardDesc,capitalize}}. Failing to {{SWITCH:vars.callingCardType,trophy,take this,callingCard,leave this}} when the opportunity arises inflicts a minor Instability on {{him}}.{{BR}}{{SWITCH:vars.callingCardType,callingCard,A calling card makes it easier for the conspiracy (or the authorities) to identify {{his}} handiwork; leaving a calling card makes this Scar count as Overt for the conspiracy's next surveillance roll.,trophy,A trophy makes it easier for {{his}} crimes to be traced to {{him}}; if investigators gain access to {{his}} trophy collection&comma; {{he}} suffers the {{TOOLTIP:Hunted Condition,json.conditions.hunted}}."
